Mar 7 2009 	Amazing Family Value for Northwest Beijing	We picked this hotel for its location, close to our son's boarding school and subway lines. We love China, but it sure was nice to be in this amazingly clean new hotel with its large beautiful clean pool and fitness center. Compared to other hotels in the area it is an amazing value, and it has the best pool we've experienced in China. Clean, comfortable rooms with comfortable beds. The high quality buffet breakfast has plenty of fresh fruits, omelets, pastries... It's a short walk to the #2 and #10 subway line so you can ride anywhere you need to go. We did have to pay extra for internet, and it was so new it wasn't on gps yet so hard to find. We are already booked to go back!	
Mar 2 2009 	Good short stay	Spend three nights at this hotel; from January 13-January 17, 2009. Upon arrival we were greeted by the bellhop, and the check in was a breeze. The room is nicely arranged with all the modern convience; the sitting stone stool in the shower is a big plus. My wife and I did utilize the gym and the indoor pool at the hotel; the free weights and treadmill keep us from gaining too much weight while indulging ourselves with good Chinese food. We had our breakfast every morning at the lobby restaurant; it is included with our room. The breakfast is good, you have your choice of American/Japanese/Chinese. However, I thought the dinner buffet was bit overpriced and the food wasn't that good. We never had the chance to dine at the other two restaurants at the establishment (Yunan cusine and Cantonese Seafood); perhaps next time around. There are plenty of restaurants near by the hotel, a short cab ride would get you there. The only negative part of this particular hotel is that it is brand new, and 3 out of 5 cab drivers required us to give them specific direction to get to the hotel. Overall, we liked this hotel: 1. the price $100 per night 2. the service 3. it is new.	
Feb 21 2009 	Great place but inconvenient location	Stayed there nearly 10 days while looking for an apartment. The price was very good and the hotel and rooms quite nice. Definitely 5-star decoration.However the location of the hotel is not convenient. It is close to nothing except some construction sites. You cannot go out in the evening for a walk, there is nothing to see, no restaurant, no shops, nothing. There is no taxi queue at the hotel so they have someone get you one from the street. The hotel is on a one-way street along the expressway. So when you get a taxi and wish to to to the city center or on Ring Road 3, the taxi is going in opposite direction and results in a detour of about 4km.On the other hand the subway (line10) is 10-15 walking distance and the best way to get around as if you take a taxi back to your hotel and even show the driver the hotel business card he will have no clue where this is. most of the time I had to help the driver with my limited mandarin.In any case, if you don't mind the location and are willing to take the subway, this ios great value.	
Nov 2 2008	Would Stay Again	We recently spent 2 nights here last week. We were pleasantly surprised with the size of the room and amenities. There is a very good breakfast buffet (by Chinese standards) that includes many pastries, an Indian section, Chinese section, Japanese section, juice, fruit, salads, hot foods with baked beans, broiled tomatoes, mushrooms, meats and to-order eggs. Also a waffle/pancake section. We never had as good a breakfast for the next 9 days. We stayed on the 12th floor. The glass shower door leaks out on the floor if it gets too much water on it. This was reported throughout our friends rooms. The views from our side of the hotel covered many of the national bird of china. The Crane. As in Construction.	
Oct 13 2008 	Yunnan comes to Beijing	A new (opened August 2008) hotel in Beijing's North East. Its got a Yunnan theme and a business/high end focus. At times there seems to be more staff waiting to serve than guests but this should hopefully improve as it becomes more widely known.Rooms are comfortable with a large bathroom. (Rainshower head and separate bath). Reported a couple of minor maintenance issues and they were fixed efficiently and graciously within 8 hours. Surrounded by construction activity, it looks a little isolated. (cannot hear construction tho, and wont last long given Beijings phenominal transformation rate).Easy to access from the third ring road if you're headed to the west but the one way road system makes it hard to reach if you are travelling the third ring road in an easterly direction. 5-10 minute walk to a subway station (Shaoyaoju). I got a electronic swipe card and travelled easily around the city. Subway has good graphics and English support for figuring out where to get on and off. Taxi rank that quickly gets you a cab if you want door to door service.Food and beverage on the dear side.Friendly staff with plenty of English speakers.(Didn't test other languages, sorry!)	
